description.narrative:
The Programme Management Unit (PMU) will be based in Oxfam, country office in Cambodia and responsible for overall and day- to-day project management and implementation. The PMU will liaise with Oxfam offices, regional partners and lead partners in-country. It will ensure adequate allocation of resources and implementation of activities as well as proper financial management.

Its role is:
# Financial management: ensuring that resources are deployed in a timely and adequate way as per the programme document;
# Collecting financial and narrative reports from regional partners and countries and collating them in the appropriate form to be submitted a) to the Steering Committee for sign off and b) Oxfam Novib, which will review for quality and donor compliance and submit to the donor;
# Designing and applying the programme#s MEAL framework; and
# Providing technical ICT support to the programme participants in the countries.
